ENTRY            C1506   20260326   20260518   20260518       C257
SUBENT        C1506001   20260326   20260518   20260518       C257
BIB                  5         11
TITLE      Structure of 12N using 11C+p resonance scattering
AUTHOR     (K.Perajarvi,C.Fu,G.V.Rogachev,G.Chubarian,
           V.Z.Goldberg,F.Q.Guo,D.Lee,D.M.Moltz,J.Powell,
           B.B.Skorodumov,G.Tabacaru,X.D.Tang,R.E.Tribble,
           B.A.Brown,A.Volya,J.Cerny)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,74,024306,2006)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.74.024306
INSTITUTE  (1USABRK,1USATAM,1USAFSU,1USANOT,1USAMSU)
HISTORY    (20070119C) DR
           (20260313A) BP: Corrected subentries 2-3, added DOI,
                      separated metadata for the both experiments.
ENDBIB              11
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           14
SUBENT        C1506002   20260326   20260518   20260518       C257
BIB                  9         34
REACTION   (1-H-1(6-C-11,EL)1-H-1,,DA)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,1USABRK) Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory's
            (LBNL) 88-inch cyclotron.
INC-SPECT  Berkeley: 10-MeV proton cyclotron was used as a
           driver accelerator, producing 11C, which was then
           transported as CO2 and injected into the Advanced ECR
           ion source (AECR-U).
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) A DE (thickness 72 microm)-E (thickness 3 mm)
           Si-detector telescope was mounted on one scattering
           chamber arm, about 14.6 cm away from the target at
           Berkeley
SAMPLE     Berkeley: The target ladder held a 12.4-mg/cm2-thick
           nickel degrader followed by a 18.4-mg/cm2-thick (CH2)n
            (= polyethylene) foil.
METHOD     (TTM) Thick target inverse kinematics (TTIK) method
           at Berkeley includes two measurements. a) The setup
           for the 2.2- to 6.6-MeV excitation energy interval:
           Measurements at 0 degree were made possible by using
           the thick target inverse kinematics (TTIK) method.
           In addition to 0 degree data, measurements at 15
           degree in the laboratory were also carried out.
           b) The setup for the 6.5- to 11.0-MeV excitation energy
            interval Measurements were performed at small angles
            (0, 5, and 10 degree in the laboratory) to maximize
           the counting statistics.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Uncertainties related to the absolute
           normalizations are not included in the given error
            bars; includes some uncertainty in the corresponding
           proton background.
STATUS     (CURVE,,K.Perajarvi+,J,PR/C,74,024306,2006) For 5,10
           degr. data taken from Figs. 3 to 5.
           (TABLE,,K.Perajarvi+,J,PR/C,74,024306,2006) For 0 and
           15 degree, data received from K. Perajarvi on 2/27/2007
HISTORY    (20260313A) BP: Corrected subentry metadata.
ENDBIB              34
NOCOMMON             0          0
